                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13647451" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 12:36:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The query fails because CallStatementNode passes a null SubqueryList into bindExpression(), which subsequently fails when trying to add a SubqueryNode to the null list. One simple fix might be to make CallStatementNode pass a non-null SubqueryList argument and check that it&apos;s empty after the statement has been bound. It still won&apos;t be possible to use sub-queries as arguments to CALL statements, but at least they would fail with a syntax error rather than a NullPointerException.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13647455" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 12:51:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Link to derby-user thread about this bug: &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/201304.mbox/%3CAC7EE6BD73B6B247A98C4FA5571DBDB91DAECB0C%40srv-exchange.qualiformed.lan%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/201304.mbox/%3CAC7EE6BD73B6B247A98C4FA5571DBDB91DAECB0C%40srv-exchange.qualiformed.lan%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13647457" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 13:01:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch derby-6212-01-a.diff makes CallStatementNode pass a SubqueryList to bindExpression() so that it doesn&apos;t fail with NPE if there is a sub-query. After the statement is bound, it raises a syntax error if there were any sub-queries. Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; call syscs_util.syscs_set_database_property(&apos;abc&apos;, (select max(ibmreqd) from sysibm.sysdummy1));&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR 42X74: Invalid CALL statement syntax. (errorCode = 30000)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch also adds a regression test case to LangProcedureTest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running full regression tests now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13647515" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 14:32:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;All the regression tests passed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13653644" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 10 May 2013 09:50:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1480909.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not planning to backport the fix since it&apos;s such a minor issue. But I don&apos;t think there should be any problems with backporting it in case someone wants to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
